    <author initials="O." surname="Friel" fullname="Owen Friel">
      <organization>Cisco</organization>
    </author>
    <date day="13" month="April" year="2018"/>
    <abstract>
      <t>   The pre-shared key mechanism available in TLS 1.3 is not suitable for
   usage with low-entropy keys, such as passwords entered by users.
   This document describes how the SPAKE password-authenticated key
   exchange can be used with TLS 1.3.

	 </t>
    </abstract>
